{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"cd9d3b15-2206-4e13-bd96-7548712741b5","content":"Here's the correct attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Example usage:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Waiting on API v2 migration\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Waiting on API v2 migration\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Waiting on API v2 migration\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Waiting on API v2 migration\")]\npublic void MyTunitTest() { }\n```\n\n> **Note:** xUnit is the only one where the skip reason is a property on the test attribute itself rather than a separate attribute. All four frameworks will report the test as \"skipped\" (not failed) in test results with your reason message.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8ed30526-6e55-40e0-a47e-bedabceb64a5","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about test-skipping attributes across four .NET test frameworks. This is a knowledge question I can answer directly.","outputTokens":337,"requestId":"CFC7:2E7D56:146440C:17A75EA:69EC1324"},"id":"3f9cc69a-a309-4d53-9dce-051cf8984993","timestamp":"2026-04-25T01:04:44.161Z","parentId":"8a53a6dc-0092-4574-bb99-298c0c06e015"}
